[1] Iceland
Date: Mon 4 Mar 2019
Source: Outbreak News Today [abridged, edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/iceland-reports-2nd-measles-case-31286/


Iceland health officials reported on [Sat 2 Mar 2019] a confirmed measles case in an 11-month-old child. The unvaccinated child was in the same flight as a person with infectious measles during a flight last month [February 2019].

The child was admitted to Hringinn's Children's Hospital on [Fri 1 Mar 2019]. Officials say the likelihood of further transmission is low as long as you're vaccinated.

The initial case, traveling from the Philippines on [14 Feb 2019], was onboard flights from London to Reykjavík on [14 Feb 2019] and on Air Iceland Connect from Reykjavík to Egilsstaðir.

Officials note at present there are no known additional infected individuals; however, it is possible to get infected until [7 Mar 2019], when then 3 weeks have passed since the person with measles was traveling both abroad and in Iceland.

