[6] Madagascar
Date: Mon 4 Mar 2019
Source: Yeni Safak [abridged, edited]
https://www.yenisafak.com/en/world/measles-outbreak-in-madagascar-kills-over-900-3475916


Over 900 people have died due to a measles outbreak in Madagascar, the UN children's agency UNICEF said in a statement. According to the statement issued on [Fri 1 Mar 2019], 76 871 people were infected by measles from [3 Sep 2018 -- 21 Feb 2019]. Among the infected people, 928 have died a majority of who were children.

"Over 2 million children were immunized in 25 districts. In [February 2019], 1.4 million children were vaccinated, with another 3.9 million more to follow in [March 2019]," the statement said.

The fact that measles vaccination is not mandatory in Madagascar makes it difficult to reach a large number of children.

