[8] Wisconsin
Date: Mon 4 Mar 2019
Source: Journal Sentinel [abridged, edited]
https://eu.jsonline.com/story/communities/west/news/brookfield/2019/03/04/brookfield-couple-defies-quarantine-measles-going-public-gym/3056501002/


In violation of a health-department quarantine, a Brookfield man and his wife were charged after visiting a local health club while the man had the measles.

The 2 were charged with one count each of exposing the public to communicable disease, a misdemeanor, on [1 Mar 2019] in Waukesha County Circuit Court.

The quarantine in this instance was the least restrictive form, allowing the immediate family members living within the home to enter and leave at any time because they had been vaccinated against the virus.

The individual was ordered to be quarantined in his home 24 hours a day, 7 days a week until he was either deemed non-contagious by Health and Human Services or until [7 May 2019], the complaint said.

[Byline: Karen Pilarski]

