[12] Japan (Osaka)
Date: Mon 4 Mar 2019
Source: MBS [in Japanese, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://www.mbs.jp/news/kansainews/20190304/GE000000000000026848.shtml


According to the Osaka Municipal Health Center, the new [measles] infection was confirmed in the women in their 50s who worked at Abeno Harukas main branch of Kintetsu Department Store. In department stores customers and employees who visited the "Valentine Fair" held from the end of January [2019] to the middle of February [2019] were infected with measles one after another. The woman is working on a different floor from the event venue, but that means she used a break space for employees on the same floor as the venue every day. There are 25 measles cases in this store in total, and in the case of symptoms suspected of measles, the city calls for medical examination in advance and contacts medical institutions.

