[13] Philippines: Sarangani, South Cotabato
Date: Sat 2 Mar 2019
Source: Philippine Daily Inquirer [abridged, edited]
https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1091224/3-die-of-suspected-measles-in-sarangani-south-cotabato-2?utm_expid=.XqNwTug2W6nwDVUSgFJXed.1


The Department of Health (DOH) in the Soccsksargen region said another child died of suspected measles on [Wed 27 Feb 2019] in Sarangani, raising the death toll to 3 in the region since January [2019], health officials said.

Jenny Ventura Panizales, DOH Region 12 focal person on measles eradication, said a 9-month-old child died of suspected measles in Glan, Sarangani, and another one in Alabel, Sarangani.

"The causes of death of these 2 children are (still) being validated but health workers and parents confirmed of cases of measles in their communities," Panizales said.

Last week, DOH confirmed that measles was the cause of the death of a 4-month-old baby in Polomolok, South Cotabato. The DOH has monitored 342 suspected measles in various hospitals in the region as of [27 Feb 2019]. The number is 14% higher than the 299 cases monitored in the same period last year [2018].

[Byline: Edwin O. Fernandez]

