[14] Philippines: cases
Date: Mon 4 Mar 2019
Source: Straits Times [abridged, edited]
https://www.straitstimes.com/world/world-briefs-nearly-15000-measles-cases-in-philippines


The number of measles cases in the Philippines has almost reached 15 000, even as the government steps up its campaign against a health scare surrounding the dengue vaccine Dengvaxia.

The government had recorded 14 938 cases and 238 deaths from measles as of [28 Feb 2019], Health Department Undersecretary Eric Domingo said, adding that "the number of cases is still rising".

The Philippines declared a measles outbreak in Manila early last month [February 2019] as infections and fatalities from the highly contagious respiratory viral disease spiked.

The vaccine scare was triggered by deaths allegedly caused by Dengvaxia, which has since been banned in the country. The deaths drove many parents to shun the government's free immunisation drive.

