Two more cases of measles have been identified in Canterbury bringing the number of confirmed cases to 7. The 2 new cases are a preschool-age child and a woman in her 40s, the Canterbury District Health Board said in a statement this afternoon.

Medical Officer of Health Dr. Ramon Pink said as the numbers of confirmed cases climb, the risk of getting measles increases for those not immunised.

